race.comment: FASHION FIGHTER (2) looks hardest to beat. Fitter for the three runs in, the latest a close-up third and looks ideally suited out in journey now. Gets chance. MASTER POLANSKI (8) ran very well last time when circled the field and sustained a long run but was edged out in a photo. Take beating if repeats that figure. SPIRIT ANGEL (9) found the line strongly for a great return then wasn't far away at Kerang. Fitter and extra trip a plus. Should be winding up strongly. GOLD RELAY (3) ran well fresh then was well off best last time. Fitter and does have a decent third-up record and looks well suited here. Can improve sharply. LONDON BELL (4) resumed from a long break with a big run at Colac when beaten only a length. Will be much fitter and can give a sight this line-up.
